1
00:00:07,268 --> 00:00:08,921
[tense music]

2
00:00:17,278 --> 00:00:19,541
- [Man On Radio] And President
Reagan fully endorsed

3
00:00:19,584 --> 00:00:21,673
a major new departure
in strategic doctrine.

4
00:00:21,717 --> 00:00:23,675
A plan to put 100
giant MX missiles

5
00:00:23,719 --> 00:00:26,200
in existing Minuteman silos.

6
00:00:26,243 --> 00:00:29,464
[chattering on radio]

7
00:00:54,793 --> 00:00:56,447
[tires squeal]

8
00:00:56,491 --> 00:00:57,274
- Help me.

9
00:01:12,637 --> 00:01:13,986
- What we know is her
husband's a Quantico cop

10
00:01:14,030 --> 00:01:16,467
with Marine Security Battalion.

11
00:01:18,034 --> 00:01:20,210
- [Man] Move back!

12
00:01:20,254 --> 00:01:21,429
- Jill, I'm Special Agent Leino

13
00:01:21,472 --> 00:01:22,647
with the Naval
Investigative Service.

14
00:01:22,691 --> 00:01:24,562
I need you to tell me
what happened tonight.

15
00:01:24,606 --> 00:01:26,390
- My husband was on night duty.

16
00:01:26,434 --> 00:01:29,132
I was alone and someone called
and said they were an MP

17
00:01:29,176 --> 00:01:32,135
and Spencer was
hurt in an accident.

18
00:01:32,179 --> 00:01:33,571
They said they were
sending someone

19
00:01:33,615 --> 00:01:35,443
to take me to the hospital.

20
00:01:35,486 --> 00:01:38,141
We drove to the
woods, pulled over.

21
00:01:38,185 --> 00:01:39,577
I tried to get out.

22
00:01:39,621 --> 00:01:40,665
He had a knife.

23
00:01:42,406 --> 00:01:43,581
He raped me.

24
00:01:43,625 --> 00:01:45,148
- What did he look like?

25
00:01:45,192 --> 00:01:46,062
Help us, ma'am.

26
00:01:46,106 --> 00:01:48,151
Tell us what he looked like.

27
00:01:48,195 --> 00:01:49,500
- Black man.

28
00:01:49,544 --> 00:01:51,546
- [Leino] What else, Jill?

29
00:01:51,589 --> 00:01:53,461
- [Jill] He wore glasses.

30
00:01:55,506 --> 00:01:58,814
- There's only one black
guy in the military police.

31
00:01:58,857 --> 00:02:01,121
Sounds like Scotty.

32
00:02:01,164 --> 00:02:04,254
[upbeat brass music]

33
00:02:20,705 --> 00:02:21,924
- Scotty!

34
00:02:21,967 --> 00:02:24,361
I need to speak to you ASAP.

35
00:02:28,757 --> 00:02:30,062
- Yes, Sergeant?

36
00:02:30,106 --> 00:02:31,499
Something wrong?

37
00:02:32,543 --> 00:02:34,893
- A woman was raped last night.

38
00:02:34,937 --> 00:02:36,808
Stabbed, left for dead.

39
00:02:37,896 --> 00:02:39,289
- Who?

40
00:02:39,333 --> 00:02:41,030
- Spencer Ames' wife.

41
00:02:42,423 --> 00:02:44,642
Well, you know
Spencer, don't you?

42
00:02:44,686 --> 00:02:46,470
- I trained with him.

43
00:02:46,514 --> 00:02:47,515
We used to carpool.

44
00:02:47,558 --> 00:02:49,473
He lived in my complex.

45
00:02:50,866 --> 00:02:52,172
- Well, we're searching
what appears to be

46
00:02:52,215 --> 00:02:53,782
the crime scene now.

47
00:02:55,262 --> 00:02:57,133
- What did this guy look like?

48
00:02:57,177 --> 00:02:59,527
- It was a black guy, glasses.

49
00:03:02,965 --> 00:03:04,532
Jill says he called
and identified himself

50
00:03:04,575 --> 00:03:08,449
as a military policeman
who works with Spencer.

51
00:03:09,798 --> 00:03:12,496
- I'm the only black man in MP.

52
00:03:14,411 --> 00:03:18,720
- Naval investigators would
like to speak to you, Scotty.

53
00:03:18,763 --> 00:03:19,547
Get in.

54
00:03:21,157 --> 00:03:23,725
[subdued music]

55
00:03:25,161 --> 00:03:27,729
[engine starts]

56
00:03:42,222 --> 00:03:43,440
- I'm here with Lori Jackson,

57
00:03:43,484 --> 00:03:45,921
head of the Women for
Equal Social Justice,

58
00:03:45,964 --> 00:03:47,357
who has just won
her civil lawsuit

59
00:03:47,401 --> 00:03:49,446
against the owner
of a local diner

60
00:03:49,490 --> 00:03:51,318
who is refusing to serve blacks.

61
00:03:51,361 --> 00:03:54,538
Ms. Jackson marched with Dr.
King and continues the crusade.

62
00:03:54,582 --> 00:03:57,193
Ms. Jackson, any further
comments you'd like to make?

63
00:03:57,237 --> 00:03:58,368
- Yes, I would.

64
00:03:58,412 --> 00:04:01,415
This is not just
about a local diner.

65
00:04:01,458 --> 00:04:03,286
I want the people out
there to understand

66
00:04:03,330 --> 00:04:04,722
that this is the 80's.

67
00:04:04,766 --> 00:04:06,289
And if they think we're
not paying attention

68
00:04:06,333 --> 00:04:08,030
to what's going
on, they're wrong.

69
00:04:08,073 --> 00:04:09,597
They think they can
hide and continue

70
00:04:09,640 --> 00:04:11,338
the same old prejudiced ways,

71
00:04:11,381 --> 00:04:13,427
but I want them to know
we're gonna find them,

72
00:04:13,470 --> 00:04:14,819
we're gonna smoke them out,

73
00:04:14,863 --> 00:04:16,647
we're gonna sue them in
every court in this land,

74
00:04:16,691 --> 00:04:18,519
and we're gonna win.

75
00:04:18,562 --> 00:04:19,563
- [Reporter] That
was Lori Jackson

76
00:04:19,607 --> 00:04:21,348
of Women for Equal
Social Justice.

77
00:04:21,391 --> 00:04:23,175
Now, back to Jim in the studio.

78
00:04:23,219 --> 00:04:26,440
- Maybe she can help us
with our organization.

79
00:04:26,483 --> 00:04:29,530
[phone ringing]

80
00:04:29,573 --> 00:04:30,618
Hello?

81
00:04:32,359 --> 00:04:33,882
Yes, he is.

82
00:04:33,925 --> 00:04:35,449
Just a moment.

83
00:04:35,492 --> 00:04:38,278
It's the military police again.

84
00:04:39,975 --> 00:04:40,758
- Hello?

85
00:04:41,585 --> 00:04:43,370
Yes, this is Lindsey Scott.

86
00:04:43,413 --> 00:04:44,240
I'm here.

87
00:04:47,809 --> 00:04:50,551
- I hate those damn calls.

88
00:04:50,594 --> 00:04:53,467
You've never violated
your house arrest.

89
00:04:53,510 --> 00:04:56,557
Why they gotta be calling
you every five times a day?

90
00:04:56,600 --> 00:04:58,820
- It's just procedure, Lola.

91
00:04:58,863 --> 00:05:01,475
It's the way the system works.

92
00:05:05,217 --> 00:05:05,957
- All right, Dena baby.

93
00:05:06,001 --> 00:05:06,871
What do you think?

94
00:05:06,915 --> 00:05:08,569
- You look beautiful, Mama.

95
00:05:08,612 --> 00:05:09,396
- Teresa?

96
00:05:10,614 --> 00:05:12,268
- I think you should've
gotten a new dress.

97
00:05:12,312 --> 00:05:14,836
That old thing smells
like moth balls.

98
00:05:14,879 --> 00:05:16,446
- Thanks a lot, honey.

99
00:05:16,490 --> 00:05:19,319
- Just giving my opinion.

100
00:05:19,362 --> 00:05:20,407
- Aunt Lily.

101
00:05:20,450 --> 00:05:21,408
- Oh, look at you.

102
00:05:21,451 --> 00:05:22,974
You're beautiful.

103
00:05:24,498 --> 00:05:25,673
- And you're looking good.

104
00:05:25,716 --> 00:05:26,717
Always will.

105
00:05:29,459 --> 00:05:32,375
- I got something for you.

106
00:05:32,419 --> 00:05:33,289
- No.

107
00:05:33,333 --> 00:05:34,682
- Mm-hmm.

108
00:05:34,725 --> 00:05:35,813
Look at this.

109
00:05:40,122 --> 00:05:43,517
- That's Cousin Terry's
good luck charm.

110
00:05:45,562 --> 00:05:47,651
I didn't know we still had it.

111
00:05:47,695 --> 00:05:50,480
- I'd never lose this.

112
00:05:50,524 --> 00:05:51,525
He loved it.

113
00:05:53,483 --> 00:05:55,398
You were his little minnow.

114
00:05:55,442 --> 00:05:59,228
And I know he'd want
you to wear it, dear.

115
00:05:59,271 --> 00:06:01,404
You're getting too old to
be getting married anymore,

116
00:06:01,448 --> 00:06:02,753
so I just figured it might help.

117
00:06:02,797 --> 00:06:04,581
[both laugh]

118
00:06:04,625 --> 00:06:06,409
Of course, now you know I've
been looking for a new man

119
00:06:06,453 --> 00:06:09,369
for 40 years and it
ain't done me no good.

120
00:06:09,412 --> 00:06:11,936
[both laugh]

121
00:06:16,550 --> 00:06:17,551
- Thank you.

122
00:06:19,422 --> 00:06:20,380
- Yes, baby.

123
00:06:24,471 --> 00:06:27,387
Now, where's my Dena and Teresa?

124
00:06:27,430 --> 00:06:30,781
Come on over here and
give your old aunt a kiss.

125
00:06:30,825 --> 00:06:33,567
[subdued music]

126
00:06:40,269 --> 00:06:42,750
[woman crying]

127
00:06:52,542 --> 00:06:55,110
[bell ringing]

128
00:06:55,153 --> 00:06:59,375
["Wedding March"
playing on organ]

129
00:07:25,401 --> 00:07:28,404
[soft guitar music]

130
00:07:38,806 --> 00:07:40,503
- What are you doing?

131
00:07:44,551 --> 00:07:47,510
- Just following
tradition, darling.

132
00:07:50,034 --> 00:07:51,514
Over the threshold.

133
00:07:55,431 --> 00:07:56,563
Whoa.

134
00:07:56,606 --> 00:07:57,520
It's gonna be a
little crowded in here

135
00:07:57,564 --> 00:07:59,000
when I get all my stuff in.

136
00:07:59,043 --> 00:08:01,132
- [Lori] Oh, we'll manage.

137
00:08:01,176 --> 00:08:02,482
- I promise you one thing.

138
00:08:02,525 --> 00:08:03,831
- What's that?

139
00:08:03,874 --> 00:08:05,136
- We're gonna have that
little cabin in the woods

140
00:08:05,180 --> 00:08:06,050
you've always been
dreaming about.

141
00:08:06,094 --> 00:08:07,312
- You mean like a little house?

142
00:08:07,356 --> 00:08:08,531
- Yes, ma'am.

143
00:08:08,575 --> 00:08:09,750
- Something we
can all move into?

144
00:08:09,793 --> 00:08:12,927
- Yes, and we will make
love all night long.

145
00:08:19,586 --> 00:08:20,587
- Teresa?

146
00:08:21,805 --> 00:08:22,589
Teresa?

147
00:08:24,199 --> 00:08:25,766
You know what time to
pick up Dena from school

148
00:08:25,809 --> 00:08:29,247
and don't forget the PTA
meeting on Thursday night.

149
00:08:29,291 --> 00:08:31,075
Now, if the people
from the NAACP call,

150
00:08:31,119 --> 00:08:32,990
give them the
number at the hotel.

151
00:08:33,034 --> 00:08:37,255
And Aunt Lily's in charge
of all emergencies.

152
00:08:37,299 --> 00:08:39,649
I don't know how I'm
gonna get everything done.

153
00:08:39,693 --> 00:08:42,434
- I've got two jobs
to worry about.

154
00:08:42,478 --> 00:08:46,482
If I can take time off
for a week, so can you.

155
00:08:46,526 --> 00:08:47,570
- I'm trying, I'm trying.

156
00:08:47,614 --> 00:08:49,050
Believe me.

157
00:08:49,093 --> 00:08:52,096
You know how much I'm
looking forward to this trip?

158
00:08:52,140 --> 00:08:54,534
- Mama, you're not
leaving for two more days

159
00:08:54,577 --> 00:08:55,883
and you're already packed?

160
00:08:55,926 --> 00:08:58,059
- Ain't nothing wrong
with being organized.

161
00:08:58,102 --> 00:08:59,756
Now, you're gonna
water all the plants

162
00:08:59,800 --> 00:09:00,931
and don't you and
your sister eat

163
00:09:00,975 --> 00:09:03,107
that sugar cereal all day long.

164
00:09:03,151 --> 00:09:04,805
- Don't worry about us.

165
00:09:04,848 --> 00:09:06,546
[door opens]

166
00:09:06,589 --> 00:09:08,156
- Here's the mail, Mama.

167
00:09:08,199 --> 00:09:10,245
Looks like somebody
had a lot to say.

168
00:09:10,288 --> 00:09:11,594
- Thanks, baby.

169
00:09:21,212 --> 00:09:23,780
[subdued music]

170
00:09:37,489 --> 00:09:41,668
Now, tell me what you were
doing the day of the assault.

171
00:09:42,973 --> 00:09:45,410
- Well, I finished
cleaning the apartment

172
00:09:45,454 --> 00:09:47,456
and then I went to
Dumphrey's Drug Store

173
00:09:47,499 --> 00:09:50,677
and bought my wife a foot
massager for her birthday.

174
00:09:50,720 --> 00:09:52,592
I wanted to get
her something else,

175
00:09:52,635 --> 00:09:54,768
so I drove to Zayre's
on Woodbridge,

176
00:09:54,811 --> 00:09:57,814
it's about 20 miles
away, to look.

177
00:09:57,858 --> 00:10:00,077
I didn't find anything.

178
00:10:00,121 --> 00:10:01,731
- Now, you said
something in your letter

179
00:10:01,775 --> 00:10:03,603
about buying a Coke.

180
00:10:03,646 --> 00:10:05,387
- Yeah, from some
white counter girl.

181
00:10:05,430 --> 00:10:07,215
Her friend called her Pam.

182
00:10:07,258 --> 00:10:08,651
Now, I told my lawyer,

183
00:10:08,695 --> 00:10:11,393
but he said since the NIS
had already talked to her.

184
00:10:11,436 --> 00:10:12,524
- [Lori] NIS?

185
00:10:12,568 --> 00:10:14,004
- The Naval
Investigative Services.

186
00:10:14,048 --> 00:10:15,266
- [Lori] I see.

187
00:10:15,310 --> 00:10:16,485
- Since they had
already talked to her,

188
00:10:16,528 --> 00:10:17,747
and she didn't
recognize my picture,

189
00:10:17,791 --> 00:10:19,096
there was nothing he could do.

190
00:10:19,140 --> 00:10:22,273
- But, you can't prove
you were at Zayre's?

191
00:10:22,317 --> 00:10:23,318
- No, ma'am.

192
00:10:23,361 --> 00:10:24,667
- What does your lawyer think?

193
00:10:24,711 --> 00:10:26,060
- Mr. Kuhnke?

194
00:10:26,103 --> 00:10:27,496
[scoffs]

195
00:10:27,539 --> 00:10:29,541
He says we have
nothing to worry about

196
00:10:29,585 --> 00:10:31,500
because they have no evidence.

197
00:10:31,543 --> 00:10:33,458
But, he's not the one on trial.

198
00:10:33,502 --> 00:10:34,677
- Mm-mm.

199
00:10:34,721 --> 00:10:36,244
- You also said that
you wanted me to contact

200
00:10:36,287 --> 00:10:37,637
a Lieutenant Colonel...

201
00:10:37,680 --> 00:10:39,639
- Colonel Harry.

202
00:10:39,682 --> 00:10:41,510
Here's his address,
his phone number.

203
00:10:41,553 --> 00:10:43,077
You can talk to him.

204
00:10:43,120 --> 00:10:45,688
And this here is from
the Article 32 hearing.

205
00:10:45,732 --> 00:10:49,083
It's like the military
grand jury hearing.

206
00:10:49,126 --> 00:10:51,955
- Corporal Scott,
I'm an activist.

207
00:10:51,999 --> 00:10:54,697
I'm not an investigator
or an attorney.

208
00:10:54,741 --> 00:10:57,918
I've picketed, I've
marched, I've filed suits,

209
00:10:57,961 --> 00:11:00,660
but this is a
whole new ballgame.

210
00:11:15,413 --> 00:11:17,589
I'll take a look at it.

211
00:11:17,633 --> 00:11:19,591
- My court martial's
in two weeks.

212
00:11:19,635 --> 00:11:22,203
- I'll read it, but no promises.

213
00:11:29,036 --> 00:11:31,691
- [Lindsey] You're the
only one I heard from.

214
00:11:31,734 --> 00:11:32,692
- Excuse me?

215
00:11:34,389 --> 00:11:36,957
- I wrote 25 letters
and you're the only one

216
00:11:37,000 --> 00:11:39,437
who took the time to see us.

217
00:11:40,612 --> 00:11:42,614
Mrs. Jackson, thank you.

218
00:11:49,099 --> 00:11:51,580
[bell dinging]

219
00:11:59,588 --> 00:12:00,458
- [Man] How are you doing today?

220
00:12:00,502 --> 00:12:02,025
- Fine.

221
00:12:02,069 --> 00:12:04,506
I'm looking for Lieutenant
Colonel Richard Harry.

222
00:12:04,549 --> 00:12:05,768
I believe he owns this place.

223
00:12:05,812 --> 00:12:06,595
- And you are?

224
00:12:06,638 --> 00:12:08,553
- Lori Jackson.

225
00:12:08,597 --> 00:12:13,036
Lindsey Scott suggested
I speak to Colonel Harry.

226
00:12:13,080 --> 00:12:14,995
- All right, I'm Harry.

227
00:12:17,171 --> 00:12:20,217
I was a military
trial magistrate.

228
00:12:20,261 --> 00:12:21,566
It was my job to
determine if there was

229
00:12:21,610 --> 00:12:25,135
sufficient evidence
to charge him.

230
00:12:25,179 --> 00:12:25,962
- And?

231
00:12:27,094 --> 00:12:29,487
- They had nothing.

232
00:12:29,531 --> 00:12:32,360
They even had the
FBI do two lab tests.

233
00:12:32,403 --> 00:12:33,143
Nothing.

234
00:12:33,187 --> 00:12:34,536
No forensic evidence,

235
00:12:34,579 --> 00:12:36,799
nothing to link him to the
crime in any way at all.

236
00:12:36,843 --> 00:12:38,496
He didn't have a
rock-solid alibi,

237
00:12:38,540 --> 00:12:43,153
but without any evidence I
didn't think it mattered.

238
00:12:43,197 --> 00:12:44,981
- Why did it go ahead?

239
00:12:46,243 --> 00:12:48,942
- I ordered him released.

240
00:12:48,985 --> 00:12:51,683
The next day I
was retired early.

241
00:12:54,034 --> 00:12:55,078
Command influence.

242
00:12:55,122 --> 00:12:56,645
- What does that mean?

243
00:12:56,688 --> 00:13:00,562
- What that means is that his
superiors determine his fate.

244
00:13:01,911 --> 00:13:04,131
If they think you're guilty,

245
00:13:04,174 --> 00:13:06,960
then by Heaven you
are going down.

246
00:13:08,483 --> 00:13:09,789
And by his actions, a
base commander sent a very

247
00:13:09,832 --> 00:13:12,835
clear message to any future
members of the court.

248
00:13:12,879 --> 00:13:14,445
You find him guilty.

249
00:13:31,680 --> 00:13:35,336
- [gasps] How could I forget?

250
00:13:35,379 --> 00:13:36,685
Our first rally together.

251
00:13:36,728 --> 00:13:37,860
- Mm-hmm.

252
00:13:37,904 --> 00:13:40,645
- And not just our first rally.

253
00:13:48,436 --> 00:13:49,480
- What is all this?

254
00:13:49,524 --> 00:13:50,525
- [Lori] Hmm?

255
00:13:50,568 --> 00:13:51,352
- What's this?

256
00:13:51,395 --> 00:13:52,353
This here?

257
00:13:52,396 --> 00:13:53,876
- Oh.

258
00:13:53,920 --> 00:13:57,619
Oh, I met with that
young guy Lindsey Scott.

259
00:13:57,662 --> 00:14:01,014
I spent the last hour
reading his court transcript.

260
00:14:01,057 --> 00:14:01,841
- Oh, no.

261
00:14:03,277 --> 00:14:04,582
I know that look.

262
00:14:06,758 --> 00:14:10,110
Listen, that look
stays in Virginia

263
00:14:10,153 --> 00:14:12,939
'cause they don't allow
that look in Hawaii.

264
00:14:12,982 --> 00:14:15,855
- They are looking
to railroad this guy.

265
00:14:15,898 --> 00:14:17,421
They want to send him
right into Leavenworth

266
00:14:17,465 --> 00:14:20,294
for the rest of his life
for something he didn't do.

