linking Corporal
Scott with the victim?

528
00:26:37,813 --> 00:26:41,643
- It was all negative
or inconclusive.

529
00:26:41,687 --> 00:26:43,863
- Thank you, Agent Lindner.

530
00:26:43,906 --> 00:26:46,561
[tense music]

531
00:26:48,737 --> 00:26:50,609
- After he raped me,

532
00:26:52,785 --> 00:26:54,656
he started to choke me.

533
00:26:57,354 --> 00:27:01,576
I tried to push his arms
away and then I blacked out.

534
00:27:03,186 --> 00:27:06,668
When I woke up, he
was standing over me,

535
00:27:06,712 --> 00:27:10,890
and he had the knife in his
hands, and he was laughing.

536
00:27:13,414 --> 00:27:14,676
- Do you see the man
who did this to you

537
00:27:14,720 --> 00:27:17,244
in the courtroom today?

538
00:27:17,287 --> 00:27:18,811
- Yes, sir.

539
00:27:18,854 --> 00:27:22,292
- Would you please point him
out to the members of the jury?

540
00:27:27,515 --> 00:27:29,430
- This man right there.

541
00:27:31,432 --> 00:27:32,476
- This government
has no more questions

542
00:27:32,520 --> 00:27:35,044
for this witness, Your Honor.

543
00:27:39,658 --> 00:27:43,357
- Ms. Ames, I don't
mean to upset you,

544
00:27:43,400 --> 00:27:46,403
but if I do, it's just
to get at the truth.

545
00:27:46,447 --> 00:27:50,669
At the physical lineup you
identified two men, didn't you?

546
00:27:52,192 --> 00:27:55,978
And you said you were sorry,
but you couldn't be sure.

547
00:27:56,022 --> 00:27:58,546
- I was 99.9% sure.

548
00:27:58,589 --> 00:28:02,550
- But, didn't you say you were
sorry you couldn't be sure?

549
00:28:05,422 --> 00:28:06,597
- Yes.

550
00:28:06,641 --> 00:28:08,382
[people chattering]

551
00:28:08,425 --> 00:28:09,426
- Thank you.

552
00:28:11,385 --> 00:28:13,387
- Is that what Kuhnke
calls a cross-examination?

553
00:28:13,430 --> 00:28:14,997
I mean, for God's sake.

554
00:28:15,041 --> 00:28:16,956
He didn't even press her on
the fact that she knew Scott.

555
00:28:16,999 --> 00:28:18,305
Her husband was
friends with her.

556
00:28:18,348 --> 00:28:19,654
I mean, why didn't
she just come out

557
00:28:19,698 --> 00:28:21,264
and say it was Lindsey Scott,

558
00:28:21,308 --> 00:28:22,962
the black guy who
lives in my building?

559
00:28:23,005 --> 00:28:25,181
It's not like her husband had
a lot of black co-workers.

560
00:28:25,225 --> 00:28:26,400
He only had one.

561
00:28:27,793 --> 00:28:28,707
Mr. Kuhnke.

562
00:28:31,448 --> 00:28:32,319
Mr. Kuhnke!

563
00:28:38,107 --> 00:28:40,719
[phone ringing]

564
00:28:50,903 --> 00:28:51,730
- Hello?

565
00:28:55,821 --> 00:28:57,170
It's Kuhnke.

566
00:28:57,213 --> 00:28:58,737
Honey, it's Kuhnke.

567
00:29:07,441 --> 00:29:08,224
- Hello?

568
00:29:10,096 --> 00:29:10,879
Mm-hmm.

569
00:29:14,622 --> 00:29:16,667
Why are you calling me now?

570
00:29:17,973 --> 00:29:21,847
I tried to have this
conversation with you hours ago.

571
00:29:21,890 --> 00:29:23,892
[sighs]

572
00:29:23,936 --> 00:29:25,546
You know, if Lindsey
Scott's life wasn't

573
00:29:25,589 --> 00:29:29,768
hanging in the balance I would
just tell you to go to hell.

574
00:29:29,811 --> 00:29:30,638
Uh-huh.

575
00:29:30,681 --> 00:29:31,552
All right.

576
00:29:31,595 --> 00:29:32,640
Okay.

577
00:29:35,599 --> 00:29:37,688
[groans]

578
00:29:39,429 --> 00:29:41,780
[yawns]

579
00:29:41,823 --> 00:29:44,217
Now, he wants me to round
up all the witnesses

580
00:29:44,260 --> 00:29:47,568
that he should've talked
to a long time ago.

581
00:29:47,611 --> 00:29:48,961
God, what an idiot.

582
00:29:49,004 --> 00:29:50,440
Should've known.

583
00:29:54,575 --> 00:29:57,578
[people chattering]

584
00:29:59,580 --> 00:30:01,800
He'll be in a few minutes.

585
00:30:16,423 --> 00:30:20,166
Mr. Kuhnke, I got all
the witnesses you wanted.

586
00:30:20,209 --> 00:30:21,689
Everybody's here but Ruby.

587
00:30:21,732 --> 00:30:22,472
- I see.

588
00:30:22,516 --> 00:30:24,213
Well, where is she?

589
00:30:25,519 --> 00:30:26,868
I need her now.

590
00:30:26,912 --> 00:30:28,174
- [Lori] Well, I don't know.

591
00:30:28,217 --> 00:30:29,610
I think she's on her
way here, I hope.

592
00:30:29,653 --> 00:30:31,481
I know she hasn't had time
to look at her records.

593
00:30:31,525 --> 00:30:33,875
- Time is of the essence.

594
00:30:33,919 --> 00:30:36,443
- By the way, you're welcome.

595
00:30:46,540 --> 00:30:47,410
Oh, Ruby.

596
00:30:47,454 --> 00:30:48,150
Please, answer the phone.

597
00:30:48,194 --> 00:30:49,412
Sister, be there.

598
00:30:53,547 --> 00:30:54,591
Ruby!

599
00:30:56,332 --> 00:30:58,465
I'm so glad you got my message.

600
00:30:58,508 --> 00:30:59,901
They want to put you
on the stand next.

601
00:30:59,945 --> 00:31:00,684
- What?

602
00:31:00,728 --> 00:31:01,468
- Yes.

603
00:31:01,511 --> 00:31:02,338
- Girl, no.

604
00:31:02,382 --> 00:31:03,339
You must be out of your mind.

605
00:31:03,383 --> 00:31:04,732
No, my hair's a mess.

606
00:31:04,775 --> 00:31:06,386
I didn't even have any time
to put any stockings on.

607
00:31:06,429 --> 00:31:07,648
And honey, nevermind the makeup.

608
00:31:07,691 --> 00:31:08,431
Oh, no.

609
00:31:08,475 --> 00:31:09,476
I cannot do this.

610
00:31:09,519 --> 00:31:10,390
- Don't fret.

611
00:31:10,433 --> 00:31:12,261
You're black, you're beautiful,

612
00:31:12,305 --> 00:31:15,482
and you're here to save the day.

613
00:31:15,525 --> 00:31:18,050
- Ms. Hills, did
you see the accused,

614
00:31:18,093 --> 00:31:22,750
Corporal Lindsey Scott, on
the 20th of April, 1983?

615
00:31:22,793 --> 00:31:24,056
- Well, sir.

616
00:31:24,099 --> 00:31:25,535
That's kind of hard
for me to pinpoint

617
00:31:25,579 --> 00:31:28,887
whether I saw him on April 20th.

618
00:31:28,930 --> 00:31:32,542
- You don't know if you
saw him on April 20th?

619
00:31:32,586 --> 00:31:36,807
- I remember the last time
I saw him was in the Spring.

620
00:31:38,853 --> 00:31:41,856
[people chattering]

621
00:31:43,336 --> 00:31:46,469
- [Kuhnke] No more
questions, Your Honor.

622
00:31:46,513 --> 00:31:49,211
- [Judge] The witness
will step down.

623
00:31:49,255 --> 00:31:50,996
If the defense doesn't
have any more witnesses

624
00:31:51,039 --> 00:31:55,261
to call at this time, the
court will take a brief recess.

625
00:31:57,306 --> 00:31:59,787
[woman crying]

626
00:32:04,618 --> 00:32:06,968
[tense music]

627
00:32:10,058 --> 00:32:12,191
- We, the members of the jury,

628
00:32:12,234 --> 00:32:15,455
find the accused,
Corporal Lindsey Scott,

629
00:32:15,498 --> 00:32:18,762
guilty on all counts and
sentence him to be confined

630
00:32:18,806 --> 00:32:21,243
to hard labor for 30 years

631
00:32:21,287 --> 00:32:25,073
and his rank to be reduced
to that of private.

632
00:32:27,293 --> 00:32:28,076
- Oh, no.

633
00:32:29,034 --> 00:32:31,471
No, he's not guilty.

634
00:32:31,514 --> 00:32:32,602
He's not guilty!

635
00:32:32,646 --> 00:32:34,561
Please, listen to me.

636
00:32:35,649 --> 00:32:36,693
Please, listen!

637
00:32:36,737 --> 00:32:37,999
Leave him alone!

638
00:32:38,043 --> 00:32:39,392
Leave him alone!

639
00:32:39,435 --> 00:32:40,610
He's not guilty!

640
00:32:41,742 --> 00:32:43,178
No, Lindsey!

641
00:32:43,222 --> 00:32:44,223
Lindsey!

642
00:32:44,266 --> 00:32:45,180
Lindsey!

643
00:32:45,224 --> 00:32:47,443
Don't touch me, don't touch me!

644
00:32:47,487 --> 00:32:48,923
Let him go!

645
00:32:48,967 --> 00:32:50,359
Let him go!

646
00:32:50,403 --> 00:32:52,187
He's not guilty!

647
00:32:52,231 --> 00:32:53,406
He's not guilty.

648
00:32:55,103 --> 00:32:57,714
[subdued music]

649
00:33:06,549 --> 00:33:07,942
- [Man] Well, this
isn't the first time

650
00:33:07,986 --> 00:33:10,423
we've ran into this problem
and he's said that to us.

651
00:33:10,466 --> 00:33:11,380
[phone ringing]

652
00:33:11,424 --> 00:33:12,947
- Well, why don't you tell him?

653
00:33:12,991 --> 00:33:16,559
- [Man] Well, I spoke to
her husband last night.

654
00:33:16,603 --> 00:33:18,518
- Howard and Howard.

655
00:33:18,561 --> 00:33:19,998
Can I help you?

656
00:33:20,041 --> 00:33:20,781
One moment, please.

657
00:33:20,824 --> 00:33:21,782
[phone ringing]

658
00:33:21,825 --> 00:33:23,392
Howard and Howard.

659
00:33:23,436 --> 00:33:24,654
No, I'm sorry.

660
00:33:24,698 --> 00:33:25,960
Mr. Leino is on
another phone call.

661
00:33:26,004 --> 00:33:27,048
Hold, please.

662
00:33:28,093 --> 00:33:29,355
Can I help you?

663
00:33:29,398 --> 00:33:32,532
- Yeah, I'm here
to see Mr. Leino.

664
00:33:32,575 --> 00:33:34,273
- [Secretary] Do you
have an appointment?

665
00:33:34,316 --> 00:33:35,056
- Lori Jackson.

666
00:33:35,100 --> 00:33:36,275
He's expecting me.

667
00:33:36,318 --> 00:33:38,451
- One moment, please.

668
00:33:38,494 --> 00:33:41,367
- Do you have a restroom
I could use real quick?

669
00:33:41,410 --> 00:33:43,151
- [Secretary] Yeah, it's
down the hall to the left.

670
00:33:43,195 --> 00:33:44,631
- Oh, thank you.

671
00:33:46,415 --> 00:33:49,984
[people chattering]

672
00:33:50,028 --> 00:33:50,767
- [Man] No, I'm sorry.

673
00:33:50,811 --> 00:33:51,681
I don't know her.

674
00:33:51,725 --> 00:33:54,032
Take a number and a message.

675
00:33:55,381 --> 00:33:56,469
Lori Jackson.

676
00:33:57,383 --> 00:33:58,427
- That's me.

677
00:34:00,342 --> 00:34:02,562
I'm with Women for
Equal Social Justice.

678
00:34:02,605 --> 00:34:04,303
I think you should take
a look at this brief.

679
00:34:04,346 --> 00:34:05,565
It's concerning the case

680
00:34:05,608 --> 00:34:07,523
United States versus
Corporal Lindsey Scott.

681
00:34:07,567 --> 00:34:09,438
Now, he was wrongfully
convicted of a crime

682
00:34:09,482 --> 00:34:10,961
he did not commit
and I think that...

683
00:34:11,005 --> 00:34:11,745
- Excuse me.

684
00:34:11,788 --> 00:34:12,833
Whoa, whoa.

685
00:34:12,876 --> 00:34:15,270
I am familiar with the case.

686
00:34:16,576 --> 00:34:18,534
Please, have a seat.

687
00:34:18,578 --> 00:34:20,058
Take a deep breath.

688
00:34:21,537 --> 00:34:22,538
- Thank you.

689
00:34:25,150 --> 00:34:27,543
- So, how did you get my name?

690
00:34:27,587 --> 00:34:29,545
- Well, someone told
me about your firm.

691
00:34:29,589 --> 00:34:32,331
They said it was the best
criminal law firm in town.

692
00:34:32,374 --> 00:34:35,116
They also said it was
impossible to get an appointment

693
00:34:35,160 --> 00:34:37,423
unless you called a month
in advance, or were rich,

694
00:34:37,466 --> 00:34:39,338
or came with someone's
recommendation.

695
00:34:39,381 --> 00:34:43,516
Well, I'm not rich, I don't
have a month, so I improvised.

696
00:34:43,559 --> 00:34:46,432
I, however, am
recommending myself.

697
00:34:47,694 --> 00:34:51,350
- New cases have to go
through the partners.

698
00:34:51,393 --> 00:34:53,265
- You're not a partner?

699
00:34:54,266 --> 00:34:55,093
- No.

700
00:34:56,006 --> 00:34:56,746
- Oh.

701
00:34:56,790 --> 00:34:58,096
- Wait a second.

702
00:34:58,139 --> 00:35:00,489
That doesn't mean
I can't help you.

703
00:35:02,230 --> 00:35:03,144
Talk to me.

704
00:35:08,193 --> 00:35:11,370
- Is an ineffectual defense
a reason for a new trial?

705
00:35:11,413 --> 00:35:14,590
- Yes, it's called
a Dubay hearing.

706
00:35:16,418 --> 00:35:19,465
Okay, you convince me this
isn't a total waste of time

707
00:35:19,508 --> 00:35:21,945
so I can convince my bosses.

708
00:35:24,122 --> 00:35:25,123
- All right.

709
00:35:34,871 --> 00:35:36,438
- [Leino] Excuse me, Mr. Howard.

710
00:35:36,482 --> 00:35:37,222
- [Mr. Howard] Yes, John.

711
00:35:37,265 --> 00:35:38,571
What is it?

712
00:35:38,614 --> 00:35:40,703
- I just met with a
woman, Lori Jackson,

713
00:35:40,747 --> 00:35:42,575
about the Lindsey Scott case.

714
00:35:42,618 --> 00:35:44,272
- Marine out of Quantico?

715
00:35:44,316 --> 00:35:45,839
Military appeals.

716
00:35:45,882 --> 00:35:48,407
Messy business, especially
appealing the government.

717
00:35:48,450 --> 00:35:49,234
Look out.

718
00:35:51,584 --> 00:35:54,413
- She said the defense
was not quite up to par.

719
00:35:54,456 --> 00:35:57,981
Now, I told her a Dubay hearing
was a long shot at best.

720
00:35:58,025 --> 00:36:00,767
It's difficult to prove any
defense team was ineffectual.

721
00:36:00,810 --> 00:36:01,681
- Look out.

722
00:36:04,423 --> 00:36:05,206
- Um.

723
00:36:07,556 --> 00:36:08,470
What do you think?

724
00:36:08,514 --> 00:36:10,603
- What do you think?

725
00:36:10,646 --> 00:36:12,257
- Well, she has a good case.

726
00:36:12,300 --> 00:36:14,128
- Military appeals.

727
00:36:14,172 --> 00:36:15,477
Read it.

728
00:36:15,521 --> 00:36:17,523
You have your first case.

729
00:36:17,566 --> 00:36:20,439
And tell them we'll
do it pro bono.

730
00:36:20,482 --> 00:36:21,570
- By myself?

731
00:36:21,614 --> 00:36:22,528
Alone?

732
00:36:22,571 --> 00:36:23,833
- As counsel.

733
00:36:23,877 --> 00:36:25,879
Take Myers here
if you need help.

734
00:36:25,922 --> 00:36:27,097
- Sir.

735
00:36:27,141 --> 00:36:28,360
- You can be co-counsels.

736
00:36:28,403 --> 00:36:30,057
It's about time you
two started getting

737
00:36:30,100 --> 00:36:31,580
some courtroom exposure.

738
00:36:31,624 --> 00:36:32,494
- Yes, sir.

739
00:36:34,322 --> 00:36:35,149
- [Mr. Howard] Leino.

740
00:36:35,193 --> 00:36:36,455
- Yes, sir?

741
00:36:36,498 --> 00:36:40,502
- Take a few lessons from
Myers on how to dress.

742
00:36:40,546 --> 00:36:41,460
- Yes, sir.

743
00:36:42,939 --> 00:36:45,725
What's wrong with
the way I dress?

744
00:36:47,335 --> 00:36:49,598
- I don't know what
you want from me,

745
00:36:49,642 --> 00:36:51,948
but I love the Marine Corps.

746
00:36:51,992 --> 00:36:53,254
I always have.

747
00:36:54,473 --> 00:36:57,519
I don't blame the corps
for this, I blame the NIS.

748
00:36:57,563 --> 00:36:59,913
I was a good Marine
and they had no right

749
00:36:59,956 --> 00:37:02,437
to treat me the way they did.

750
00:37:04,091 --> 00:37:07,268
I just want to be a
good Marine again.

751
00:37:12,621 --> 00:37:13,622
- Mr. Leino?

752
00:37:16,408 --> 00:37:19,541
- I respect your
conviction, Private.

753
00:37:21,848 --> 00:37:23,937
We'll see what we can do.

754
00:37:26,026 --> 00:37:28,420
[knocking on glass]

755
00:37:28,463 --> 00:37:29,638
- Well, that's time.

756
00:37:29,682 --> 00:37:30,552
- Right.

757
00:37:37,559 --> 00:37:38,778
You hang in there.

758
00:37:38,821 --> 00:37:39,953
- Yes, sir.

759
00:37:39,996 --> 00:37:40,997
- All right.

760
00:37:42,434 --> 00:37:44,174
- [Lori] I'll talk to you soon.

761
00:37:44,218 --> 00:37:45,219
- All right.

762
00:37:54,576 --> 00:37:56,361
- Myers was in the Army
and I was a Marine.

763
00:37:56,404 --> 00:37:58,841
Myers was in a high-profile
case where he defended a man

764
00:37:58,885 --> 00:38:02,541
accused of misdeeds in the
My Lai massacre in Vietnam.

765
00:38:02,584 --> 00:38:05,544
Lori Jackson, this
is Gary Myers.

766
00:38:06,458 --> 00:38:07,459
- Nice to meet you.

767
00:38:07,502 --> 00:38:08,373
- Likewise.

768
00:38:09,374 --> 00:38:10,592
I'm glad you made it back.

769
00:38:10,636 --> 00:38:13,508
Listen, there's some
things we need to go over.

770
00:38:13,552 --> 00:38:14,379
- Like what?

771
00:38:14,422 --> 00:38:16,119
- Well, Mrs. Jackson.

772
00:38:16,163 --> 00:38:19,035
John and I need to hash
out some legal issues here,

773
00:38:19,079 --> 00:38:21,255
so if you would excuse us.

774
00:38:21,299 --> 00:38:23,170
- So, the ignorant black
woman just steps aside

775
00:38:23,213 --> 00:38:26,608
and let the Harvard
boys do their thing?

776
00:38:28,523 --> 00:38:30,612
- This is as much your
case as it is ours.

777
00:38:30,656 --> 00:38:33,093
- This is not just a case to me.

778
00:38:33,136 --> 00:38:34,007
This is a cause.

779
00:38:34,050 --> 00:38:34,921
There's a big difference.

780
00:38:34,964 --> 00:38:36,488
Now, let me be perfectly clear.

781
00:38:36,531 --> 00:38:38,446
I look out for Lindsey Scott,

782
00:38:38,490 --> 00:38:41,754
so I need to know
what's going on.

783
00:38:41,797 --> 00:38:43,582
So, where do we start?

784
00:38:47,760 --> 00:38:48,543
Thank you.

785
00:38:57,683 --> 00:38:59,598
I have something
important to say

786
00:38:59,641 --> 00:39:02,165
and I hope you'll understand.

787
00:39:06,561 --> 00:39:10,609
Lindsey's lawyers have made
a motion for a retrial.

788
00:39:10,652 --> 00:39:12,654
- What does that have
to do with all of us?

789
00:39:12,698 --> 00:39:15,483
- It means I'm going to be
working with Leino and Myers

790
00:39:15,527 --> 00:39:18,486
and it could drag on
for quite some time.

791
00:39:18,530 --> 00:39:19,444
- How long?

