01:01:12,451 --> 01:01:13,452
We're burning daylight.

1176
01:01:13,495 --> 01:01:14,235
- You didn't.

1177
01:01:14,279 --> 01:01:15,759
I can't believe it.

1178
01:01:23,636 --> 01:01:24,942
It's beautiful.

1179
01:01:24,985 --> 01:01:26,421
- [Paul] Mm-hmm.

1180
01:01:40,522 --> 01:01:42,916
- [Both] Welcome home, Mama.

1181
01:01:44,178 --> 01:01:46,485
[laughs]

1182
01:01:46,528 --> 01:01:49,096
- [Dena] Don't you love it?

1183
01:01:49,140 --> 01:01:50,837
- I love it.

1184
01:01:50,881 --> 01:01:52,578
- Come on, have a seat.

1185
01:01:52,621 --> 01:01:54,406
- Congratulations, Mama.

1186
01:01:54,449 --> 01:01:56,495
Isn't it the best?

1187
01:01:56,538 --> 01:01:57,496
- It's the best.

1188
01:01:57,539 --> 01:01:59,019
- See?

1189
01:01:59,063 --> 01:02:00,194
It's big enough for the girls
to have their own bedrooms.

1190
01:02:00,238 --> 01:02:02,675
Office for you, office for me.

1191
01:02:02,719 --> 01:02:04,416
And it's so private.

1192
01:02:04,459 --> 01:02:08,812
Bad guys are gonna have
a hard time finding us.

1193
01:02:08,855 --> 01:02:10,770
- It's beautiful.

1194
01:02:10,814 --> 01:02:12,337
You're beautiful.

1195
01:02:13,599 --> 01:02:14,513
I love you.

1196
01:02:16,297 --> 01:02:18,299
I love you so very much.

1197
01:02:22,173 --> 01:02:22,956
Thank you.

1198
01:02:36,970 --> 01:02:38,276
- Here we go.

1199
01:02:38,319 --> 01:02:39,799
Military's equivalent
of the Supreme Court.

1200
01:02:39,843 --> 01:02:41,932
We lose here, we're done.

1201
01:02:43,455 --> 01:02:47,067
Myers is presenting
the opening statement.

1202
01:02:54,074 --> 01:02:56,468
- Every man has a
right to a fair trial

1203
01:02:56,511 --> 01:03:01,168
and a fair trial includes
adequate legal counsel.

1204
01:03:01,212 --> 01:03:03,040
If the court case
were a horse race,

1205
01:03:03,083 --> 01:03:05,172
this would be like putting
one jockey on a track

1206
01:03:05,216 --> 01:03:06,565
without a horse.

1207
01:03:06,608 --> 01:03:09,481
That is not fair,
that is not legal.

1208
01:03:09,524 --> 01:03:12,789
That is not how our
justice system works.

1209
01:03:14,268 --> 01:03:17,706
Lindsey Scott's original
defense lawyer, Ervin Kuhnke,

1210
01:03:17,750 --> 01:03:21,536
did not prepare an alibi defense
for the inexplicable reason

1211
01:03:21,580 --> 01:03:25,236
that he didn't think the
case would go to trial.

1212
01:03:25,279 --> 01:03:27,455
The linkage between
Mr. Kuhnke's conduct

1213
01:03:27,499 --> 01:03:30,502
and the conclusion of the
case was palpable and clear.

1214
01:03:30,545 --> 01:03:32,765
We end up with no
preparation whatsoever

1215
01:03:32,809 --> 01:03:35,637
and we end up with a conviction.

1216
01:03:37,117 --> 01:03:38,815
The practice of
criminal law involves

1217
01:03:38,858 --> 01:03:40,686
getting your shoes dirty.

1218
01:03:40,729 --> 01:03:43,994
All Mr. Kuhnke did
was sit at his desk.

1219
01:04:05,580 --> 01:04:07,931
[knocking on door]

1220
01:04:07,974 --> 01:04:08,975
- Mr. Myers.

1221
01:04:09,933 --> 01:04:11,586
- Hey, Lori.

1222
01:04:11,630 --> 01:04:14,111
After all this time, it's Gary.

1223
01:04:18,463 --> 01:04:22,380
- Listen, I spoke to my
source at the Washington Post.

1224
01:04:22,423 --> 01:04:25,339
She heard about a
Major Ron McNeil

1225
01:04:25,383 --> 01:04:27,341
who's at the Marine JAG
Office at Camp Lejueune.

1226
01:04:27,385 --> 01:04:29,300
Have you heard of him?

1227
01:04:29,343 --> 01:04:31,519
- Toughest prosecutor
the marine Corps has.

1228
01:04:31,563 --> 01:04:32,869
What about him?

1229
01:04:34,305 --> 01:04:36,481
- Well, she heard that
he's been ordered to report

1230
01:04:36,524 --> 01:04:39,788
to Quantico to start
prepping a big case.

1231
01:04:43,662 --> 01:04:45,969
- You know what this means?

1232
01:04:47,492 --> 01:04:51,191
- Looks like we're winning
the appeal and they're scared.

1233
01:04:56,588 --> 01:04:57,371
Good work.

1234
01:04:59,069 --> 01:05:00,070
- Thank you.

1235
01:05:04,596 --> 01:05:05,858
- I can't believe it.

1236
01:05:05,902 --> 01:05:06,641
Finally.

1237
01:05:06,685 --> 01:05:07,947
Oh, John.

1238
01:05:07,991 --> 01:05:08,817
Good job.

1239
01:05:12,256 --> 01:05:13,648
Thank you.

1240
01:05:13,692 --> 01:05:15,259
Yeah.

1241
01:05:15,302 --> 01:05:17,087
I'll talk to you soon.

1242
01:05:23,136 --> 01:05:24,355
It's official.

1243
01:05:25,443 --> 01:05:28,228
Lindsey Scott is coming home.

1244
01:05:28,272 --> 01:05:29,534
At least for now.

1245
01:05:29,577 --> 01:05:31,928
- I'm sick and tired
of Lindsey Scott.

1246
01:05:31,971 --> 01:05:32,841
- Oh, honey.

1247
01:05:32,885 --> 01:05:33,668
Don't be such a sourpuss.

1248
01:05:33,712 --> 01:05:34,539
Ow.

1249
01:05:37,150 --> 01:05:39,631
- Mama, you don't look so good.

1250
01:05:39,674 --> 01:05:41,198
- What?

1251
01:05:41,241 --> 01:05:42,547
- You heard me.

1252
01:05:45,028 --> 01:05:46,507
- Oh, don't be such
a sourpuss, honey.

1253
01:05:46,551 --> 01:05:49,423
We have so much to
celebrate about.

1254
01:05:51,556 --> 01:05:53,950
[door creaks]

1255
01:05:57,127 --> 01:06:00,521
- Why are you in
here so much lately?

1256
01:06:00,565 --> 01:06:03,655
- Just trying to get settled in.

1257
01:06:03,698 --> 01:06:06,179
Taking on some extra clients.

1258
01:06:07,964 --> 01:06:10,836
- That's not what
I'm asking about.

1259
01:06:13,491 --> 01:06:14,492
Mama's sick.

1260
01:06:17,277 --> 01:06:21,499
- Yeah, well she's been
under a lot of stress lately.

1261
01:06:22,543 --> 01:06:23,762
- Really sick.

1262
01:06:28,158 --> 01:06:29,507
Don't you care?

1263
01:06:34,642 --> 01:06:35,948
- Clean sheets.

1264
01:06:36,862 --> 01:06:37,994
Dena did the laundry.

1265
01:06:38,037 --> 01:06:39,517
Can you believe it?

1266
01:06:39,560 --> 01:06:40,605
- Sweetheart.

1267
01:06:40,648 --> 01:06:41,388
- Yeah?

1268
01:06:41,432 --> 01:06:42,737
- Teresa knows.

1269
01:06:44,261 --> 01:06:45,523
- Did you tell her?

1270
01:06:45,566 --> 01:06:48,526
- Two-stepped around it.

1271
01:06:48,569 --> 01:06:49,309
But, I think it's time.

1272
01:06:49,353 --> 01:06:51,094
She's got to be told.

1273
01:06:51,137 --> 01:06:53,139
- I'm just waiting
for the right time.

1274
01:06:53,183 --> 01:06:55,794
- Honey, there is no right time.

1275
01:06:58,579 --> 01:06:59,624
- Soon.

1276
01:07:01,495 --> 01:07:02,670
Soon, I promise.

1277
01:07:05,369 --> 01:07:07,980
[subdued music]

1278
01:07:21,863 --> 01:07:23,648
- Excuse me, Dr. Sturla?

1279
01:07:23,691 --> 01:07:25,737
- [Dr. Sturla] Mm-hmm?

1280
01:07:25,780 --> 01:07:28,000
- I'm Lori Jackson's daughter.

1281
01:07:28,044 --> 01:07:31,264
I need to talk to
you about my mother.

1282
01:07:32,613 --> 01:07:35,573
[typewriter clacking]

1283
01:07:38,445 --> 01:07:39,446
- [Lori] Coffee?

